---
description: UI rules for the Civitas Command Center
alwaysApply: true
---

The Command Center is an internal operating system, not just an admin panel.

UI principles:
- Calm, structured, editorial, high-signal interface.
- Prefer clarity over dashboard clutter.
- Design for operational use: capture, organize, relate, decide, publish.
- The internal UI should reflect systems thinking, not generic CRUD screens.
- Avoid overbuilding controls before the information architecture is stable.